<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKNOTE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS RETURN TO SQUARE ONE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   VANCOUVER, B.C. _ So now, with a horrific road trip in their
past, Robert Horry rejoining them at present and Dennis Rodman in
their immediate future, the Lakers' season starts anew.
</P>
<P>
   In third-grader lingo, it's a do-over. Starting today.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you're gonna drop a bomb on this team,'' said Rick Fox,
``you might as well drop it now, when we're in disarray to begin
with. Let's get (Rodman) in here and somehow try to build some
rhythm from that point on.''
</P>
<P>
   The rebuilding project starts with an impromptu practice at the
Forum this afternoon, right after introductions. And Team Chaos
might yet find some stability in the Worm Era.
</P>
<P>
   The team planned to have Rodman sign his contract after Tuesday
night's game _ thus delaying a roster move _ and Horry received
medical clearance earlier in the day after missing seven games with
an irregular heartbeat.
</P>
<P>
   Whether Rodman revives a suddenly listless team or drags it
further into the abyss will soon be determined. Coach Del Harris
has consulted John Lucas, who coached Rodman in San Antonio, and
Chicago Bulls assistant Frank Hamblen, and has decided to use the
tried-and-true approach with Rodman _ the long leash.
</P>
<P>
   ``It has worked for Chicago and for John Lucas at San Antonio,
to allow Dennis a good deal of personal freedom,'' Harris said.
</P>
<P>
   Even if that means Rodman's Rules are a little different than
those for his teammates.
</P>
<P>
   ``Being on a team is a matter of give-and-take,'' Harris said.
``The key element is to be a team man . . . and on and off the
court. We will allow Dennis to be Dennis.''
</P>
<P>
   Or, as Fox said, ``The more of a collar you put on him, the more
his actions rare up. He's a product of negation.''
</P>
<P>
   And can this young team and its coach handle the Dennis Show?
</P>
<P>
   ``We know he's going to wear high heels and dresses and go off
to Vegas to get married,'' Kobe Bryant said, ``but I can put up
with that for a championship ring.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman will be in uniform for Thursday night's game against the
Clippers and will be the starting power forward as soon as he's
ready.
</P>
<P>
   __ Heartening diagnosis: Horry was cleared to play by team
doctors Tuesday, 10 days after being diagnosed with an irregular
heartbeat.
</P>
<P>
   Tests did not pinpoint a specific cause for Horry's irregular
heartbeat, but doctors believe it was brought on by a viral
infection. He will be able to play without any restrictions or any
risk, team spokesman John Black said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Ouch report: To make room for Rodman on the roster, the
Lakers will probably place rookie Ruben Patterson on the injured
list today. Patterson came down with a sudden case of right-knee
tendinitis Tuesday night and did not dress for the game.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
