<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MAIN25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    De Niro an ex-Cold Warrior on a mission in `Ronin'
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Ronin'' (R)
</P>
<P>
   Think of it as a postmodern action movie. This guilty pleasure
from director John Frankenheimer casts Robert De Niro as a member
of an ad hoc band of secret warriors, along with Jean Reno, Stellan
Skarsgard and Sean Bean. Former Cold War operatives cut loose from
their agencies, they're now free agents for hire. This time,
they've been recruited by Natascha McElhone, a mysterious
Irishwoman who wants them to get their hands on a suitcase. What's
in it? Doesn't matter. It's just the MacGuffin that gives
Frankenheimer an excuse to whip up some very tense, very cool
action scenes in some beautiful European locales. (The movie is
also on DVD, $24.98.)
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
