<P>
   CENSUS _ WASHINGTON _ The Census Bureau will conduct a
traditional head count for congressional reapportionment, but a
Clinton administration official says the bureau plans to use
statistical sampling for all other purposes in the 2000 census. At
the census news conference today, Southeastern Legal Foundation
Director Matt Glavin says he will again sue over the sampling plan.
(Sherman, Cox News Service)
