<P>
   GLF-MATCH (Carlsbad, Calif.) _ The highly anticipated Anderson
Consulting Match Play Championship begins with 32 head-to-head
matches. It's a five-day tournament, with a Final Four on Saturday
and a 36-hole final on Sunday. By Clifton Browne.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ARATON-COLUMN (Port St. Lucie, Fla.) _ Sports of The Times
column: Major league baseball has fired a warning shot at its
umpires, with a recent memo warning them to call the strike zone as
it is spelled out in the rule book, which means calling strikes on
pitches above the belt. Who better to comment on this tug-of-war
than Rickey Henderson, one of the great leadoff hitters of all time
and a batter who sometimes seems bent in half at the plate in an
effort to shrink his own strike zone. By Harvey Araton.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-MCGWIRE (Jupiter, Fla.) _ Mark McGwire officially begins his
1999 season by meeting with reporters on his first full day of
spring training. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NETS-BLAZERS (East Rutherford, N.J.) _ Portland at the Nets,
7:30 p.m. ET start. By Chris Broussard.
</P>
