</P>
<P>
   Leon Reed hopes to hold political office one day. On this night,
the 30-year-old Texas Christian University senior is looking the
part, dressed in a coat and tie with a closely cropped haircut
framing his narrow, dark-brown face. When he takes his place behind
the lectern to introduce Don Jackson, chairman of TCU's political
science department, he sounds the part as well. But this is not a
political rally. It is a meeting Reed has organized to inform his
fellow students, whose skin color has put them at the center of an
intensive manhunt by Fort Worth and campus police, of their rights.
By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story will move in ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
 &QL;
