<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PICKLES, PIMENTOS PUNCH UP GELATIN SALAD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Mary Doebbeling sends in a couple of recipes for the requested
gelatin salad that included dill pickles and pimentos.
</P>
<P>
   Jane Youngblood of Aledo, Texas, sends her version of cornflake
cookies.
</P>
<P>
   A MERRY-MERRY RECIPE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   20-ounce can crushed pineapple, including juice
</P>
<P>
   4-ounce jar pimentos, including juice, finely chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup finely chopped dill pickles
</P>
<P>
   10 finely minced spearmint leaves
</P>
<P>
   3 1/4 tablespoons dill vinegar (or plain vinegar plus minced
dill)
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons plain gelatin (measure from 2 or more envelopes)
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup cold water
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients except gelatin and water. Stir
thoroughly, cover, and refrigerate at least an hour to blend the
flavors.
</P>
<P>
   Pour gelatin into cold water. Then, in a double boiler, melt it
over hot water and stir it into the pineapple mixture.
</P>
<P>
   Pour into 8 individual molds or a 6-cup mold and refrigerate.
This salad is nice served with a green-tinted mayonnaise made by
adding minced leaves of mint and dill, and dill vinegar and
pineapple juice.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 134 calories, trace fat, 32
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 362 milligrams
sodium, 1 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   PICKLE SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8-10
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 tablespoons unflavored gelatin
</P>
<P>
   1 cup of cold water
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup dill pickle juice
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup pineapple juice
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup juice from pimentos
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   2 large dill pickles, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup pimentos, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 cup pecans, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 cup crushed pineapple, drained well
</P>
<P>
   Dissolve gelatin in cold water and set aside.
</P>
<P>
   Combine sugar, all juices and salt in saucepan and bring to
boil. Mix the gelatin into the hot juice mixture and stir to
dissolve. Place in refrigerator until almost congealed.
</P>
<P>
   When the mixture is ready, add pickles, pimentos, pecans and
crushed pineapple.
</P>
<P>
   Pour into a ring mold or a mold of any other shape, and chill
until firm. Unmold on a bed of greens and serve with sour cream or
mayonnaise.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 191 calories, 7 grams fat, 30
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 836 milligrams
sodium, 35 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   DOUBLE CRUNCH COOKIE
</P>
<P>
   Yields 6 dozen
</P>
<P>
   1 cup butter or margarine
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 cup light or dark brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   2 eggs
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon milk
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   2 cups flour
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon baking powder
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   2 cups granola
</P>
<P>
   2 cups slightly crushed unsweetened cornflakes
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chocolate chips
</P>
<P>
   1 cup coarsely chopped, toasted, natural unblanched almonds
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cream butter and sugars. Beat in
eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix flour with baking soda, baking powder
and salt. Mix into creamed mixture. Add granola, cornflakes,
chocolate chips and chopped almonds. Stir and mix with large spoon
until thoroughly combined. Drop by teaspoons onto well-oiled (or
sprayed) baking sheets. Flatten slightly with fork. Bake 10 to 15
minutes or until lightly browned and done. Remove from baking sheet
while still warm. Cool on racks.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per cookie: 101 calories, 6 grams fat, 12
grams carbohydrates, 1 gram protein, 6 milligrams cholesterol, 77
milligrams sodium, 49 percent of calories from fat.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
