<HEADER>
A7680 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-VEGGIE-CHEF-1600(2ndT     02-24 0716
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VEGGIE-CHEF-1600(2ndTake)_TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VEGGIE OUT WITH CURTIS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JUNE NAYLOR RODRIGUEZ 
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED: vacationing in Antigua. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It's not clear what kind of sauteed vegetables Aikens will find
in the United Kingdom, but with his positive outlook, he'll surely
prevail.
</P>
<P>
   BOK CHOY-SHIITAKE STIR-FRY
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   1/2 pound shiitake mushrooms, washed and sliced
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   3 cloves garlic, minced
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon grated fresh ginger
</P>
<P>
   1 head of bok choy, chopped into 1-inch or smaller pieces
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup chopped red bell peppers
</P>
<P>
   1 bunch green onions, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon dark sesame oil
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons sweet sherry
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   Salt to taste
</P>
<P>
   8 to 12 ounces Oriental noodles, cooked
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons sesame seeds, for garnish
</P>
<P>
   In large skillet, saute mushrooms in oil for 3 to 5 minutes. Add
garlic, ginger, bok choy, peppers, green onions, sesame oil,
sherry, soy sauce and salt. Stir fry until the bok choy and peppers
are tender, about 5 to 8 minutes. Add noodles and mix. Serve on
platter and garnish with sesame seeds.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 329 calories, 12 grams fat, 50
grams carbohydrates, 11 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 989
milligrams sodium, 32 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   CARROT CAKE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   Cake:
</P>
<P>
   2 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 cup vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup carrot juice
</P>
<P>
   4 large eggs, beaten
</P>
<P>
   2 cups all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   3 teaspoons baking powder
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons baking soda
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons ground cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1 pound carrots, peeled and grated
</P>
<P>
   Icing:
</P>
<P>
   3/4 stick butter, softened
</P>
<P>
   10 ounces cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   2 1/2 cups powdered sugar
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons grated orange rind for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   Grease and flour 2 baking pans. In large bowl, combine sugar,
oil and carrot juice. Add eggs and mix well. In another bowl, sift
together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, stirring in the
carrots. Pour into prepared pans and bake for about 45 minutes or
until an inserted straw or toothpick comes out clean. Allow cake to
cook before icing.
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, beat together the butter and cream cheese until
fluffy. Add vanilla and sugar and beat until the ingredients
combine until the icing is smooth. Don't overbeat. Spread over the
cake and sprinkle with finely grated orange rind.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 982 calories, 53 grams fat,
120 grams carbohydrates, 11 grams protein, 221 milligrams
cholesterol, 792 milligrams sodium, 48 percent of calories from
fat.
</P>
<P>
   SPAGHETTI GORGONZOLA
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   5 whole green onions, minced
</P>
<P>
   2 garlic cloves, peeled and minced
</P>
<P>
   1/2 pound snow peas
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons dried coriander
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup dry white wine
</P>
<P>
   1 pound spaghetti, cooked
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   4 ounces gorgonzola cheese, crumbled
</P>
<P>
   Saute green onions, garlic, snow peas and coriander in the olive
oil and white wine for 5 to 6 minutes. Pour the spaghetti into the
vegetable mixture and combine. Season with salt and pepper, then
top with gorgonzola and serve.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 600 calories, 14 grams fat, 93
grams carbohydrates, 23 grams protein, 25 milligrams cholesterol,
525 milligrams sodium, 21 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   BEAN SALAD
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup freshly squeezed lime juice
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup chopped cilantro
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon ground cumin
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   2 cups lima beans, cooked
</P>
<P>
   1 cup black beans, cooked
</P>
<P>
   1 cup red kidney beans, cooked
</P>
<P>
   1/2 green bell pepper, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/2 red bell pepper, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped red onion
</P>
<P>
   2 cups sweet corn kernels
</P>
<P>
   In large mixing bowl, combine olive oil, lime juice, cilantro,
cumin, salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients and toss until
mixture is thoroughly blended.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 285 calories, 14 grams fat, 33
grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 11 milligrams
sodium, 46 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
