<P>
   JASPER-SENTENCE (Jasper, Texas) _ Many African-Americans believe
the death penalty has throughout history been unfairly meted out to
blacks. Now they await nervously as a mostly white jury will decide
whether a white man convicted of brutally killing a black man will
be sentenced to death. The case brings to the surface undercurrents
of mistrust and lack of faith in the justice system. By ALLAN
TURNER.
</P>
