<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Kiwi halts trips to Atlanta
 &HT;    By Scott Thurston
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Kiwi International Air Lines is ending Atlanta service
Friday, citing a shortage of planes and a shift in strategy.
</P>
<P>
   Kiwi has served Atlanta since its 1992 founding by ex-Eastern
Airlines workers. But the schedule had shrunk to just two daily
Atlanta-Newark flights because of financial troubles lingering from
a 1996 bankruptcy filing. The carrier, which now operates just four
planes, is focusing on flights between New York and Puerto Rico and
Florida, a spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   Thurston writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution
</P>
