<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Holyfield predicts Lewis falling in 3rd
 &HT;    By Jeff Schultz
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Evander Holyfield thinks pressure is the best way to
defeat Lennox Lewis. But Wednesday, he might have shifted the
pressure to himself.
</P>
<P>
   Holyfield predicted he would knock out Lewis in the third round
when the two meet in a heavyweight title unification March 13 in
New York. Holyfield has forecast victory before, but this is
believed to be the first time he has predicted a round.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's out of character for him,'' trainer Emanuel Steward
said from Lewis' training camp in the Pocono Mountains in
Pennsylvania. ``Lennox must be getting under his skin a lot, saying
things about his personal life.''
</P>
<P>
   Lewis earlier this week called Holyfield a ``hypocrite'' for
fathering children out of wedlock while claiming to be a devout
Christian.
</P>
<P>
   When Holyfield was asked on a national conference call Wednesday
about when he might retire, he responded, ``God will let me know.
That's the reason I know I'll win this fight. That's why I can say
I'm going to blow him out in the third round. If I blow him out in
the third round, it's because God wants me to _ and I will blow him
out.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
