<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Falcons' wish list includes Ambrose
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Falcons are interested in former All-Pro
cornerback Ashley Ambrose, one of the top unrestricted free agents
at his position.
</P>
<P>
   Ambrose, 28, was to visit Atlanta Wednesday, but team officials
postponed their meeting with the former Bengal.
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons want to re-sign free agent corner Ronnie Bradford,
but they probably would not, and could not, sign both him and
Ambrose.
</P>
<P>
   Cornerback Ray Buchanan will count $3 million against next
year's salary cap, and Michael Booker $1.62 million, with $1
million guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
   The 5-foot-10, 185-pound Ambrose was a second-round choice of
the Colts in 1992 and would command money similar to that of
Buchanan, his close friend and Colt teammate from 1993-95.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was going to come (Wednesday), but they want to do it
later,'' Ambrose said from Houston. ``I would be the happiest guy
in the world ... but I'm not going to cheat myself to play with
Ray. I see the money guys are getting, like Carlton Gray,'' who got
a five-year, $17 million contract with Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons would have to backload a contract for Ambrose, as
the Chiefs did with Gray. If, for example, Atlanta gave Ambrose a
four-year contract with a $2.5 million signing bonus, (like Gray's,
and the minimum $400,000 salary this season, his cap charge would
be $1.025 million for 1999.
</P>
<P>
   ``If I had a long-term deal, I wouldn't care if it was
backloaded,'' said Ambrose, who had 40 total tackles, 15 passes
defensed and two interceptions last season.
</P>
<P>
   In 1996, he was All-Pro with 57 total tackles, eight
interceptions and 20 passes defensed while playing for current
Atlanta secondary coach Ron Meeks. In 1997, he had 59 total
tackles, three interceptions and 28 passes defensed.
</P>
<P>
   If Ambrose signed with Atlanta, it might precipitate the move of
Booker, the team's 1997 first-round draft choice, to safety.
</P>
<P>
   EXTRA POINTS
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver Chris Calloway, who led the Giants in receptions
twice while playing for Atlanta coach Dan Reeves, visited the
Redskins Wednesday, and will visit the Falcons today. ... Buchanan
had an MRI on his right shoulder and will have arthroscopic surgery
to repair a ligament partially torn from his rotator cuff during
the season.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
