Keravision, a small California company. The arcs, which can be
inserted during a 10-minute procedure in an opthamologistUs office,
flatten the cornea to correct mild nearsightedness, or myopia, a
condition that affects some 22 million Americans. (Mount Sinai
Hospital/New York Times Photo)
