<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NJ-FLORIO-SENATE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FLORIO FORMS COMMITTEE TO EXPLORE HIS PROSPECTS FOR A SENATE RACE  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
   By JENNIFER PRESTON   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   TRENTON, N.J. _ Seeking to resurrect his political career,
former Gov. Jim Florio said Wednesday that he was forming an
exploratory committee to begin raising money and building support
for a possible run for the U.S. Senate seat that will be vacated by
Frank Lautenberg next year.
</P>
<P>
   Florio, who served one term before losing his re-election bid in
1993 to Christie Whitman, could end up in a rematch with Whitman,
who is also considering running for the Senate seat next year.
</P>
<P>
   Florio said he had been encouraged to seek the Democratic
nomination to the Senate by some of his old supporters. He also
said that after spending the last five years working as a college
professor and as a lawyer, he was ready to use his experience for a
new challenge. ``The time is right,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Pollsters and political experts say that Florio could win a
Democratic primary with his statewide name recognition, and run a
competitive general election campaign, although not all of the
state's Democratic Party leaders are enamored with the prospect of
his comeback.
</P>
<P>
   After Florio, as governor, pushed the state Legislature to
accept a $2.8 billion tax increase in 1990, voters punished
Democrats at the polls the next year.
</P>
<P>
   Leaders of the state Democratic Party are concerned that
Florio's candidacy would remind voters about the tax increase that
so enraged them at the time. They are also concerned that his bid
could deny the next generation of Democrats a chance to run for
statewide office. The list of Democrats considering a run include
Susan Bass Levin, the mayor of Cherry Hill, and Reps. Bob Menendez
of Union City and Frank Pallone Jr. of Long Branch.
</P>
<P>
   Whitman said Wednesday that she had not yet decided whether she
would seek the Republican nomination for the Senate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-24-99 2337EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
