<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HUSBAND-SLAIN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MURDER SUSPECT NAMED IN ATTACK ON HUSBAND'S LOVER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY DON HOLLAND  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   VENTURA, Calif. -- A month before the grisly murder of her
husband, Gladis Barreras Soto assaulted his mistress and threatened
that ``something bad'' would happen if their affair continued,
court documents showed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The mother of five crashed her car into the van of Maria C.
Ortega after seeing her husband's truck outside the woman's Oxnard
home in suburban Ventura County west of the Los Angeles area.
</P>
<P>
   Ortega sought a restraining order against Soto after the
incident and, as previously scheduled, was in court Wednesday, the
day after Soto was arrested on suspicion of shooting her husband,
Pedro Alba Barragan, in the head, then dismembering his body and
setting fire to his remains.
</P>
<P>
   ``I fear for my safety,'' Ortega said in getting the restraining
order. ``She is dangerous.''
</P>
<P>
   Court documents paint a disturbing portrait of Barragan and
Soto's 15-year marriage. He was an abusive womanizer, who
frequently used alcohol and cocaine. She was a victim of domestic
violence who, prosecutors say, retaliated during a Jan. 10 attack
on Ortega.
</P>
<P>
   Soto, 37, was charged with murder Wednesday in the slaying of
her husband.
</P>
<P>
   She had been charged with assault with a deadly weapon in
connection with the attack on Ortega and is scheduled to be
arraigned today on that charge.
</P>
<P>
   She remains jailed in lieu of $250,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   According to Ortega's request for a restraining order, Barragan
was at her home when he heard the alarm on his truck go off. When
he went outside, he saw his wife, who then got in her car and sped
past him. Moments later, Ortega returned home from an errand.
</P>
<P>
   ``When Gladis saw my van pull up, she took her car and crashed
it into mine,'' Ortega said in court records. ``She then backed up
and left.''
</P>
<P>
   In another incident, ``she cussed me out and called me a bunch
of horrible names,'' Ortega said in documents. ``She told me that I
had better stop seeing Pedro or something bad was going to happen
to me.''
</P>
<P>
   Ortega did not return a phone call Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Wednesday that Soto has told them Barragan had many
girlfriends and that he had physically and verbally abused Soto for
many years.
</P>
<P>
   Barragan, 35, pleaded no contest in 1996 to battering Soto and
was given three years' probation. In 1997, he was again arrested
for shoving his wife and yelling at her after a night of drinking.
He was sentenced to 30 days in jail for violating probation.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Barragan left his Ventura home around 7 p.m. Friday
and returned at 2 a.m. Saturday. After he fell asleep, Soto got a
small-caliber pistol and shot him in the head, police said.
</P>
<P>
   She then stuffed his body in a closet, where it remained
throughout the day. The couple's five children -- ages 6 to 11 --
were home at the time, but were unaware their father was dead,
police said.
</P>
<P>
   About 11 p.m. Saturday, Soto pulled the 5-foot-7-inch body from
the closet to the garage, where she used an electric saw to remove
his head and limbs, police said. Soto placed the head and limbs in
plastic bags.
</P>
<P>
   On Monday evening, she loaded the bags into her car, drove them
to a remote area near the Ventura River and the Ventura County
Fairgrounds, poured gasoline on them and set them ablaze, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   A transient spotted the fire and called for help.
</P>
<P>
   Using fingerprint records, authorities identified the body and
contacted Soto, who was arrested Tuesday morning. The couple's
children were placed in protective custody.
</P>
<P>
   While serving a search warrant, detectives found Barragan's
torso, along with a handgun and an electric table saw they believe
was used to dismember the body.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-24-99 2352EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
